Here lies Carnoueie, equal in merit, but, by fifty years, younger than his long-lived sire. The one got his reward sor virtue early, the other late; nor had the younger less of life’s banquet than had the elder.

XC. DE CARNUTIO, EJUSDEM FILIO.

Hic iacet aequalis meritis Carnutius, annis Longaevo decies quinque parente minor.

Hic cito, virtutis tulit alter praemia sero, Nec minus hic vitae, quam fuit ille, satur.
